WEBVTT

1
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.242
<i>Have you ever wondered
how nature gets its glow?</i>

2
00:01:01.935 --> 00:01:03.820
<i>Who gives it light and color
as the seasons come and go?</i>

3
00:01:03.843 --> 00:01:07.143
<i>Who helps all creatures,
great and small,</i>

4
00:01:07.239 --> 00:01:09.728
<i>to walk, to swim, to fly?</i>

5
00:01:12.169 --> 00:01:14.404
<i>Who crafts such tiny details?</i>

6
00:01:17.641 --> 00:01:19.775
<i>You might see them if you try.</i>

7
00:01:22.182 --> 00:01:26.787
<i>For it's all the work of fairies,
but they stay well out of sight.</i>

8
00:01:33.836 --> 00:01:38.469
<i>And the first time that a baby laughs,
a fairy's life takes flight.</i>

9
00:01:39.724 --> 00:01:41.153
<i>When the moon comes out</i>

10
00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:43.300
<i>To shine her face</i>

11
00:01:43.404 --> 00:01:46.056
<i>The birds are fast asleep</i>

12
00:01:46.157 --> 00:01:49.212
<i>And the lanterns hang from every post</i>

13
00:01:49.213 --> 00:01:52.268
The fairies leave their keep

14
00:01:52.365 --> 00:01:55.912
<i>They join their hands
and sing their songs</i>

15
00:01:56.014 --> 00:01:58.797
<i>That nary a soul can hear</i>

16
00:01:58.895 --> 00:02:01.677
<i>In the springtime
when the earth is new</i>

17
00:02:02.799 --> 00:02:06.246
<i>To the fairies they draw near</i>

18
00:02:06.351 --> 00:02:13.030
<i>To the fairies they draw near</i>

19
00:03:36.376 --> 00:03:37.871
- Hello.
- Hello.

20
00:03:37.977 --> 00:03:39.407
- Hello.
- Hi.

21
00:03:39.514 --> 00:03:41.074
- Hello.
- Hello.

22
00:03:41.754 --> 00:03:42.866
Hello?

23
00:03:43.995 --> 00:03:45.424
Queen Clarion.

24
00:03:56.284 --> 00:03:59.251
Born of laughter, clothed in cheer,

25
00:03:59.836 --> 00:04:02.040
happiness has brought you here.

26
00:04:02.555 --> 00:04:06.811
Welcome to Pixie Hollow.
I trust you found your way all right.

27
00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:08.886
I think so.

28
00:04:10.748 --> 00:04:12.985
Now, let's see about those wings.

29
00:04:54.850 --> 00:04:56.508
What are these things?

30
00:04:56.611 --> 00:04:59.261
They will help you
find your talent, little one.

31
00:04:59.362 --> 00:05:01.751
But how will I know which one is...

32
00:05:03.267 --> 00:05:04.609
You'll know.

33
00:05:55.625 --> 00:05:56.607
Hmm.

34
00:06:38.287 --> 00:06:39.245
Whoa!

35
00:06:39.342 --> 00:06:43.369
Never seen one glow that much before,
even for Vidia.

36
00:06:43.631 --> 00:06:45.192
You know,
I do believe you're right.

37
00:06:45.296 --> 00:06:48.971
Little daisy top
might be a very rare talent indeed.

38
00:06:57.135 --> 00:06:59.470
Come forward, tinker fairies,

39
00:06:59.568 --> 00:07:04.357
and welcome the newest member
of your talent guild, Tinker Bell.

40
00:07:06.449 --> 00:07:08.074
Glad we had a bath today, eh, Clank?

41
00:07:08.177 --> 00:07:09.519
- Excuse us!
- Coming through!

42
00:07:09.617 --> 00:07:11.984
Sorry! Make way for tinkers!

43
00:07:13.138 --> 00:07:16.750
Hady-hi, hady-ho, Miss Bell. I'm Clank.

44
00:07:17.362 --> 00:07:20.014
Splinters, Clank. Say it, don't spray it.

45
00:07:20.115 --> 00:07:23.464
Phineas T. Kettletree, Esquire,
at your service.

46
00:07:23.570 --> 00:07:24.764
Pleased to make your acquaintance.

47
00:07:24.787 --> 00:07:27.820
Oh, foo! He's Bobble, I'm Clank.

48
00:07:28.979 --> 00:07:30.386
Clank, Bobble.

49
00:07:31.029 --> 00:07:34.574
We're pleased as a pile of
perfectly polished pots you're here.

50
00:07:34.677 --> 00:07:35.692
Uh...

51
00:07:35.925 --> 00:07:36.884
Me, too.

52
00:07:37.973 --> 00:07:40.941
Come on, Miss Bell.
There's so much to show you.

53
00:07:43.349 --> 00:07:47.921
You've arrived
at a most wondrous and glorious time.

54
00:07:48.021 --> 00:07:49.232
Really? Why?

55
00:07:49.334 --> 00:07:52.498
Why, it's almost time
for the changing of the seasons.

56
00:07:52.598 --> 00:07:56.722
You see, here in Pixie Hollow, there are
different realms for every time of year.

57
00:07:56.822 --> 00:07:57.858
Well, there's one up ahead.

58
00:08:02.712 --> 00:08:05.811
Winter Woods. It's always cold here.

59
00:08:05.911 --> 00:08:09.359
Look there! Snowflake and frost fairies
returning home for...

60
00:08:09.464 --> 00:08:12.017
For some well-deserved rest.

61
00:08:12.121 --> 00:08:15.504
Aye. They've just finished
bringing winter to the world.

62
00:08:16.858 --> 00:08:19.411
It's the off-season
for the autumn fairies, too.

63
00:08:19.514 --> 00:08:22.678
Always practicing
that perfect shade of amber, eh?

64
00:08:22.778 --> 00:08:24.502
And the fairies of Summer Glade

65
00:08:24.602 --> 00:08:26.513
still have plenty of time to get ready.

66
00:08:26.619 --> 00:08:28.724
But not as much
as the autumn fairies,

67
00:08:28.826 --> 00:08:30.201
of course, because, well...

68
00:08:30.299 --> 00:08:33.649
Yes, Clanky. Because
right now, fairies of every talent

69
00:08:33.755 --> 00:08:36.918
are preparing for my favorite season,
springtime!

70
00:08:38.395 --> 00:08:39.355
Oh!

71
00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:45.169
Get along.
Get along, little sproutlings, and dig.

72
00:08:49.981 --> 00:08:51.322
Hello, there!

73
00:08:52.669 --> 00:08:55.833
Come on, Miss Bell.
You've got to see where we live.

74
00:09:01.949 --> 00:09:04.023
Welcome to Tinker's Nook.

75
00:09:04.126 --> 00:09:06.166
Oh, wow!

76
00:09:15.328 --> 00:09:16.288
Oh.

77
00:09:17.728 --> 00:09:20.281
Come on.
There's so much to show you.

78
00:09:42.434 --> 00:09:43.514
Cute.

79
00:09:45.411 --> 00:09:46.720
Just taking some supplies down...

80
00:09:46.820 --> 00:09:49.438
They're taking supplies
down to the workshop.

81
00:09:52.131 --> 00:09:53.440
Let her go.

82
00:09:54.052 --> 00:09:55.011
Watch out for falling...

83
00:09:55.109 --> 00:09:57.443
Watch out for falling maple seeds!

84
00:10:00.773 --> 00:10:01.787
Wow!

85
00:10:12.102 --> 00:10:15.102
And over here is where most of us live.
There's your house...

86
00:10:15.207 --> 00:10:17.411
There's your house, Tinker Bell.

87
00:10:22.599 --> 00:10:24.291
- It's mine?
- Sure is.

88
00:10:24.968 --> 00:10:27.008
We were hoping the new arrival
would be one of us,

89
00:10:27.111 --> 00:10:29.413
so we got the place all ready.

90
00:10:29.512 --> 00:10:30.853
We rounded up some work clothes...

91
00:10:30.951 --> 00:10:33.254
- We didn't know your size.
- Yes, our apologies, but...

92
00:10:33.352 --> 00:10:35.873
- But they might be too big.
- Yeah, well, that's only...

93
00:10:35.977 --> 00:10:38.050
'Cause you're so tiny.

94
00:10:38.153 --> 00:10:39.561
That'll do, Clank.

95
00:10:39.657 --> 00:10:41.926
Please come on down to the workshop
when you're ready.

96
00:10:42.025 --> 00:10:43.717
Fairy Mary will want to meet you.

97
00:10:43.818 --> 00:10:44.996
Goodbye.

98
00:10:52.682 --> 00:10:53.642
Oh.

99
00:11:36.847 --> 00:11:38.440
Stop! What?

100
00:11:39.024 --> 00:11:42.734
A five-gauge twig for an axle?
Clank, I told you it took a seven.

101
00:11:42.832 --> 00:11:43.978
Oh, you said five.

102
00:11:44.080 --> 00:11:48.042
I said seven! Oh, Clank, I tell you,
sometimes you can be pretty,

103
00:11:48.145 --> 00:11:49.356
pretty...

104
00:11:52.338 --> 00:11:54.444
So pretty.

105
00:11:56.242 --> 00:11:59.504
- Who's that, then?
- It's Tinker Bell, you snail brain.

106
00:12:02.644 --> 00:12:04.782
Wow, everyone seems so busy.

107
00:12:04.883 --> 00:12:07.272
Well, spring won't spring itself.

108
00:12:07.380 --> 00:12:11.635
Indeed, my bellowing buddy.
And we tinkers are a big part of it.

109
00:12:11.732 --> 00:12:14.034
Allow us to elucidate, Miss Bell.

110
00:12:14.836 --> 00:12:17.683
- We fiddle and fix.
- We craft and create.

111
00:12:17.780 --> 00:12:20.628
- We carve acorn buckets.
- To hold flower paint.

112
00:12:20.725 --> 00:12:23.409
- Weave saddles and satchels.
- For birdies, you see.

113
00:12:23.509 --> 00:12:26.379
- Make baskets and bushels.
- To carry the seeds!

114
00:12:26.485 --> 00:12:29.071
- When preparing for spring.
- We do all this and more!

115
00:12:29.174 --> 00:12:33.168
- Yes, being a tinker is never a bore!
- Yes, being a tinker is never a bore!

116
00:12:34.646 --> 00:12:35.725
That was great.

117
00:12:35.831 --> 00:12:40.436
So you see, Miss Bell, we help fairies
of every talent with our creations.

118
00:12:40.535 --> 00:12:44.114
Unfortunately, all those fairies
are out of luck this year.

119
00:12:44.216 --> 00:12:46.736
Unless we can actually
deliver these things to them.

120
00:12:46.840 --> 00:12:49.174
The wagon repairs are finished, I trust?

121
00:12:52.632 --> 00:12:54.193
Yes, Fairy Mary.

122
00:12:54.456 --> 00:12:57.304
- Tip-top shape.
- No wheels missing whatsoever!

123
00:12:58.682 --> 00:13:00.089
Then let's see it.

124
00:13:00.185 --> 00:13:02.520
- Ah, you see... Well...
- See,

125
00:13:02.618 --> 00:13:05.717
- with your eyes?
- Define "see," actually...

126
00:13:05.914 --> 00:13:08.566
- You have to meet Tinker Bell!
- What? Who?

127
00:13:08.795 --> 00:13:11.445
- She's new, Fairy Mary.
- Nice to meet you.

128
00:13:11.546 --> 00:13:14.296
Rapture! A new charge on whom
we can lavish

129
00:13:14.394 --> 00:13:17.013
all our tinkering wisdom and expertise!

130
00:13:19.067 --> 00:13:20.889
Let me see those hands.

131
00:13:21.724 --> 00:13:24.539
Teetering teapots, so dainty.

132
00:13:24.860 --> 00:13:28.756
Don't worry, dear. We'll build up those
tinker muscles in no time.

133
00:13:28.924 --> 00:13:29.939
Okay.

134
00:13:30.109 --> 00:13:33.524
- Now, boys, the deliveries?
- Aye, we're on it.

135
00:13:33.629 --> 00:13:36.379
As a matter of fact,
we're heading out right this second.

136
00:13:36.477 --> 00:13:40.188
- But we've only got one wheel.
- What was that?

137
00:13:40.797 --> 00:13:44.475
Nothing really,
Clank was just asking...

138
00:13:44.575 --> 00:13:46.844
If I can go as well!

139
00:13:47.295 --> 00:13:49.816
- Yeah! Good one. Very nice.
- Yes! I wondered that,

140
00:13:49.919 --> 00:13:54.197
- if you could go with us. Yes.
- That's exactly what he was saying.

141
00:13:54.752 --> 00:13:56.476
Very well. Get on with it, then.

142
00:13:58.496 --> 00:14:01.115
Slow down, Cheese, I can't keep up!

143
00:14:02.273 --> 00:14:04.182
The mouse's name is Cheese?

144
00:14:04.288 --> 00:14:07.005
Must be.
He always comes when we yell it.

145
00:14:34.180 --> 00:14:37.050
Sprinting thistles!
Bobble! Bobble!

146
00:15:11.624 --> 00:15:16.611
Easy. Easy, boy. It's all right.
Fawn's got you.

147
00:15:17.864 --> 00:15:22.088
Easy. Easy, girl. It's all right.
Silvermist's got you.

148
00:15:23.241 --> 00:15:24.616
Oh, you all right, sugar cane?

149
00:15:24.713 --> 00:15:26.056
Be careful, Rosetta, she may faint!

150
00:15:27.114 --> 00:15:29.797
Elevate her legs. No, wait.
I mean her head.

151
00:15:29.898 --> 00:15:31.731
Wait, wait, wait. Okay.
If she's red, raise the head.

152
00:15:31.755 --> 00:15:33.827
If she's pale, raise the tail.

153
00:15:34.090 --> 00:15:35.914
Does she look pale or red?

154
00:15:36.044 --> 00:15:37.735
She looks squished.

155
00:15:38.443 --> 00:15:39.556
Sorry.

156
00:15:39.788 --> 00:15:42.788
Here, let me, raindrop.
So, what happened to you, anyway?

157
00:15:42.892 --> 00:15:45.129
- Well, I...
- It was sprinting thistles!

158
00:15:46.285 --> 00:15:48.357
Those weeds are an absolute menace.

159
00:15:48.461 --> 00:15:51.757
Always trampling things,
poking people in the petunia.

160
00:15:53.166 --> 00:15:54.626
Gather round, ladies.

161
00:15:54.733 --> 00:15:56.075
We've brought some selections

162
00:15:56.172 --> 00:15:59.206
from the new spring line
of tinker specialties!

163
00:15:59.309 --> 00:16:00.836
- All right!
- Show us, show us!

164
00:16:00.942 --> 00:16:03.844
- What'd you bring?
- Your rainbow tubes, Iridessa.

165
00:16:03.950 --> 00:16:06.503
Finally! Silvermist,
could you help me?

166
00:16:16.656 --> 00:16:17.638
Oh.

167
00:16:26.353 --> 00:16:27.880
What're you gonna do with that?

168
00:16:27.985 --> 00:16:29.840
I'm gonna take it to the mainland.

169
00:16:29.937 --> 00:16:31.082
What's the mainland?

170
00:16:31.185 --> 00:16:33.128
It's where we're gonna go
change winter to spring.

171
00:16:33.234 --> 00:16:35.755
The seasons change all the time there.

172
00:16:35.923 --> 00:16:38.345
I'll get to apply my artistic sensibilities.

173
00:16:38.451 --> 00:16:41.386
Yeah. And I'll have breakfast ready
for all the wittle fuzzies

174
00:16:41.491 --> 00:16:43.400
coming out of hibernation.

175
00:16:45.364 --> 00:16:47.152
We just follow the second star...

176
00:16:47.251 --> 00:16:49.706
Ride the breeze, follow the waves...

177
00:16:49.811 --> 00:16:51.699
All the way across the sea...

178
00:16:51.795 --> 00:16:53.585
And then, there it is.

179
00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:58.254
Wow! The mainland sounds flitterific!

180
00:17:01.333 --> 00:17:04.978
Yes. The glamorous lives
of the nature-talent fairies, eh?

181
00:17:05.077 --> 00:17:06.484
We'd love to stay and chat, but...

182
00:17:06.581 --> 00:17:10.094
But we tinkers
have real work to do. Right?

183
00:17:10.198 --> 00:17:13.297
- Don't get your wings in a bunch.
- Don't be like that.

184
00:17:13.398 --> 00:17:14.773
Nice to meet you all!

185
00:17:14.870 --> 00:17:17.969
- You, too! Fly with you later!
- Fly with you later!

186
00:17:20.183 --> 00:17:21.525
Right! Here we are.

187
00:17:21.623 --> 00:17:23.695
A pretty large order of pollen pots
for the...

188
00:17:37.337 --> 00:17:39.858
Last thing is berry bushels
to deliver to the glen...

189
00:17:39.961 --> 00:17:42.101
Is it okay
if I just catch up with you later?

190
00:17:42.202 --> 00:17:43.630
Oh, I suppose.

191
00:17:44.377 --> 00:17:46.352
Can you find your way back?

192
00:17:46.681 --> 00:17:49.464
- Yeah, yeah. Sure I can.
- Well, I...

193
00:17:49.657 --> 00:17:52.113
- All right, then.
- Just be careful!

194
00:17:55.451 --> 00:17:56.410
Hi, there!

195
00:17:59.131 --> 00:18:00.277
Sorry.

196
00:18:00.668 --> 00:18:02.075
Vidia, right?

197
00:18:08.733 --> 00:18:11.450
We didn't officially meet.
I'm Tinker Bell.

198
00:18:12.221 --> 00:18:13.431
Oh, yes.

199
00:18:14.749 --> 00:18:15.895
The new girl.

200
00:18:15.997 --> 00:18:19.478
That's right! So, what's your talent?

201
00:18:21.342 --> 00:18:23.196
What do you think it is?

202
00:18:23.774 --> 00:18:29.044
You're a pollen-izer? Pollen-ator?
Pollen-picker? Pollen-plucker?

203
00:18:29.152 --> 00:18:32.632
I am a fast-flying fairy,
a true rare talent.

204
00:18:33.087 --> 00:18:35.455
And this is but a small part of what I do.

205
00:18:35.552 --> 00:18:39.064
I make breezes in the summer,
blow down leaves in the fall.

206
00:18:39.168 --> 00:18:41.852
My winds even brought you here, dear.

207
00:18:41.952 --> 00:18:44.702
Fairies of every talent depend on me.

208
00:18:45.599 --> 00:18:47.869
Hey, that's just like what I do.

209
00:18:49.217 --> 00:18:50.176
Excuse me?

210
00:18:50.305 --> 00:18:52.508
I mean, tinkers help fairies
of every talent, too.

211
00:18:52.609 --> 00:18:55.031
So we're kind of the same, you know?

212
00:18:57.314 --> 00:19:00.795
Sweetie, I make forces of nature.

213
00:19:01.283 --> 00:19:02.908
You make pots and kettles.

214
00:19:03.011 --> 00:19:07.103
I work up in the sky,
and you work down in a ditch.

215
00:19:07.747 --> 00:19:08.762
Hey!

216
00:19:08.867 --> 00:19:11.867
Don't get me wrong, sunshine.
Being a tinker is really swell and all,

217
00:19:11.972 --> 00:19:15.006
but I wouldn't go around
bragging about your talent.

218
00:19:15.108 --> 00:19:17.312
It's not like spring depends on you.

219
00:19:17.412 --> 00:19:18.874
Of course it does!

220
00:19:18.980 --> 00:19:22.429
And when I go to the mainland,
I'll prove just how important we are.

221
00:19:22.534 --> 00:19:24.421
When who goes to the mainland?

222
00:19:24.517 --> 00:19:27.234
Me, of course! For spring!

223
00:19:29.542 --> 00:19:32.096
Oh, of course. You'll prove it, huh?

224
00:19:32.390 --> 00:19:33.404
Yes, I will.

225
00:19:33.509 --> 00:19:38.016
Well, I, for one,
am looking forward to that. Excuse me.

226
00:19:39.494 --> 00:19:41.185
No. Excuse me.

227
00:19:46.535 --> 00:19:48.446
"Mine is a rare talent."

228
00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:49.662
Ugh.

229
00:19:51.337 --> 00:19:53.540
Try and tell me tinkers don't matter.

230
00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:56.029
I'll show her what a rare talent really is,
when I...

231
00:21:04.049 --> 00:21:05.031
Oh.

232
00:21:26.643 --> 00:21:29.064
- Hey, Tink, what you got there?
- Oh, hi.

233
00:21:30.291 --> 00:21:32.014
I don't know. I just found them.

234
00:21:33.363 --> 00:21:34.770
Lost things.

235
00:21:35.732 --> 00:21:37.325
- Lost things.
- Aye.

236
00:21:37.428 --> 00:21:41.225
Stuff gets lost and washes up
on Neverland from time to time.

237
00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:42.991
You know, from the mainland.

238
00:21:43.092 --> 00:21:45.133
These come from the mainland?

239
00:21:45.237 --> 00:21:47.790
That place sounds
more fascinating all the time.

240
00:21:47.893 --> 00:21:52.236
Berry bushels, check.
Pollen pots, check. Lost things, check.

241
00:21:52.951 --> 00:21:53.909
Huh?

242
00:21:54.550 --> 00:21:57.682
Lost things?
Why are you fiddling with that junk?

243
00:21:57.782 --> 00:21:59.059
Oh, um...

244
00:21:59.446 --> 00:22:01.967
Well, they were just so unusual.

245
00:22:02.071 --> 00:22:04.438
You mustn't be wasting your time
with that rubbish.

246
00:22:04.536 --> 00:22:06.992
And I won't have it
cluttering up my workshop.

247
00:22:07.096 --> 00:22:08.852
And as for you two,

248
00:22:09.625 --> 00:22:11.893
no more dilly-dallying around.

249
00:22:11.992 --> 00:22:14.295
And don't forget about
the Queen's review tonight.

250
00:22:14.393 --> 00:22:17.142
Goodness, there's still
so much to be done!

251
00:22:20.665 --> 00:22:22.007
Thank you.

252
00:22:22.649 --> 00:22:24.656
Sorry about your trinkets, Miss Bell.

253
00:22:24.761 --> 00:22:27.631
Well, we'd best be getting ready
for the review, anyway.

254
00:22:27.738 --> 00:22:29.810
What is the Queen's review?

255
00:22:29.913 --> 00:22:33.689
You see, the Queen is going to
review all the preparations for spring!

256
00:22:33.787 --> 00:22:37.617
