I don't know, Tinker Bell...

346
00:29:22.505 --> 00:29:25.059
If you could teach me your talents,
any of them,

347
00:29:25.162 --> 00:29:27.912
maybe I could show the Queen
I can work with nature, too.

348
00:29:29.419 --> 00:29:31.754
And then she'd let me go
to the mainland for spring.

349
00:29:31.850 --> 00:29:34.916
Oh, Tinker Bell.
That's just not how it works.

350
00:29:35.018 --> 00:29:37.702
- Well, maybe she could.
- She's right. She could.

351
00:29:37.803 --> 00:29:40.421
Well, I've never heard of someone
switching talents before.

352
00:29:40.523 --> 00:29:42.378
She's right. Me, neither.

353
00:29:42.539 --> 00:29:48.770
Look. You all do things that are
beautiful and magical and important.

354
00:29:49.068 --> 00:29:52.363
But me, well,

355
00:29:52.461 --> 00:29:56.039
there's gotta be more to my life
than just pots and kettles.

356
00:29:56.877 --> 00:29:59.627
All I'm asking
is that you give me a chance.

357
00:30:01.358 --> 00:30:02.732
I'll help you, Tinker Bell.

358
00:30:02.829 --> 00:30:04.422
Thank you, Sil.

359
00:30:04.526 --> 00:30:06.315
Me, too. Could be fun.

360
00:30:06.543 --> 00:30:10.317
Well, first time for everything, I guess.
What harm can come from trying?

361
00:30:10.415 --> 00:30:12.967
Well, I still think this is a bad idea.

362
00:30:15.504 --> 00:30:17.959
So, for your first day
of water fairy training,

363
00:30:18.064 --> 00:30:20.170
I could show you
how to make ripples in the pond.

364
00:30:20.272 --> 00:30:21.286
Okay!

365
00:30:21.392 --> 00:30:24.075
Or teach you how to talk
to the babbling brook.

366
00:30:24.176 --> 00:30:25.835
Oh, that sounds fun, too.

367
00:30:25.937 --> 00:30:29.035
Or wait, wait, wait.
I got it, I got it, I got it!

368
00:30:29.616 --> 00:30:32.202
Dewdrops on spider webs!

369
00:30:33.200 --> 00:30:34.924
Come on. I'll show you how to do it.

370
00:30:35.024 --> 00:30:37.294
- Good luck, Tink!
- You can do it!

371
00:30:38.834 --> 00:30:39.849
Oh, um...

372
00:30:39.954 --> 00:30:41.383
Go get 'em.

373
00:30:43.762 --> 00:30:49.392
Just cup your hands like this,
reach into the water, and...

374
00:30:50.067 --> 00:30:52.173
Okay, you've heard of a dewdrop?

375
00:30:52.276 --> 00:30:56.050
This is a don't drop.
That's water fairy humor.

376
00:30:57.076 --> 00:30:58.385
It's good.

377
00:30:58.965 --> 00:30:59.924
Come on.

378
00:30:59.988 --> 00:31:02.705
Okay, Tink, now,
this next part can be a little tricky.

379
00:31:02.805 --> 00:31:05.456
It takes a very steady,
delicate hand to...

380
00:31:08.245 --> 00:31:10.001
Where's your dewdrop?

381
00:31:10.262 --> 00:31:11.220
Oh.

382
00:31:12.629 --> 00:31:14.289
Forgot my dewdrop.

383
00:31:18.070 --> 00:31:19.314
Hey! I did

384
00:31:20.215 --> 00:31:21.175
it.

385
00:31:21.271 --> 00:31:24.532
Shake that one off. Shake it off.
You can do this!

386
00:31:27.607 --> 00:31:30.805
That's it. That's it, Tink.
You're doing it! You're...

387
00:31:32.376 --> 00:31:34.066
Now, Tink, try to...

388
00:31:34.360 --> 00:31:37.459
No, no, sweetie, you need to...
Well, maybe if you...

389
00:31:38.616 --> 00:31:41.235
Well, you have to admire
her persistence.

390
00:31:41.497 --> 00:31:42.479
Tinker Bell!

391
00:31:42.585 --> 00:31:44.789
Although, sometimes hammers glow

392
00:31:45.433 --> 00:31:46.808
for a reason.

393
00:31:52.379 --> 00:31:53.426
Whoa.

394
00:32:05.501 --> 00:32:09.756
You know, you always struck me
as a light fairy kind of gal.

395
00:32:21.245 --> 00:32:23.733
<i>Here we go in the treasure...</i>

396
00:32:27.549 --> 00:32:29.468
- Have you seen Tink?
- No, thank you. Not thirsty!

397
00:32:31.646 --> 00:32:33.534
No, no. Not "drink," Tink!

398
00:32:33.855 --> 00:32:36.408
Pink? I like purple meself!

399
00:32:36.511 --> 00:32:39.130
Tink! Have you seen Tink?

400
00:32:39.231 --> 00:32:40.311
What?

401
00:32:40.864 --> 00:32:43.798
I do not stink! Maybe it's you, eh?

402
00:32:45.825 --> 00:32:47.712
Hey, have you seen Tink?

403
00:32:49.953 --> 00:32:53.302
- Fairy Mary's gonna be cross.
- Aye, Clank.

404
00:32:53.409 --> 00:32:55.598
We'd better take some of this
off Miss Bell's plate, so...

405
00:32:55.649 --> 00:32:58.007
- All right, then.
- No, no, no! Wait, wait, Clank!

406
00:33:03.523 --> 00:33:06.426
What are...
Will you two stop mucking about?

407
00:33:06.531 --> 00:33:09.663
- What Clank did was, he took it off...
