450
00:36:40.027 --> 00:36:41.937
- You'd do well to listen to her...
- Why?

451
00:36:42.043 --> 00:36:43.898
So I can do this my whole life?

452
00:36:43.996 --> 00:36:46.899
I don't wanna be just a stupid tinker!

453
00:36:49.244 --> 00:36:52.026
No, no, not that you guys are...

454
00:36:53.436 --> 00:36:56.982
I didn't mean that... Guys, I wasn't...

455
00:36:59.164 --> 00:37:00.571
I have to go.

456
00:37:14.430 --> 00:37:19.101
Now, flap them. Flap them.
That's it! Have fun!

457
00:37:23.808 --> 00:37:25.564
Hey, Tink! You ready?

458
00:37:25.985 --> 00:37:27.578
A little nervous, actually.

459
00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:30.234
Oh, don't be silly.
Come on, you'll be fine.

460
00:37:30.337 --> 00:37:32.956
We're teaching baby birds
how to fly.

461
00:37:33.665 --> 00:37:36.186
First, you have to get their attention.

462
00:37:36.290 --> 00:37:39.040
Smile and establish trust.

463
00:37:40.130 --> 00:37:45.216
See? Okay, open your wings, honey,
and flap them up and down.

464
00:37:45.507 --> 00:37:49.401
Up and down. That's the way.
Faster, faster.

465
00:37:49.507 --> 00:37:53.248
That's right. Yes! You're doing it! Okay.
Come out this way a little bit.

466
00:37:54.211 --> 00:37:58.969
You're okay. You're okay. You got it.
Keep flapping, keep flapping!

467
00:37:59.140 --> 00:38:01.923
Hey, why don't you help
that last little guy?

468
00:38:06.692 --> 00:38:11.035
Okay, okay.
Just smile and establish trust.

469
00:38:11.462 --> 00:38:12.739
Hi, there!

470
00:38:13.574 --> 00:38:17.371
Hey, little fella,
you wanna do some flap-flap today?

471
00:38:18.854 --> 00:38:20.796
