for the rest of my life,

484
00:38:58.410 --> 00:39:00.321
I am holding you
personally responsible.

485
00:39:01.995 --> 00:39:03.817
Hey, hey. Look at this!

486
00:39:04.012 --> 00:39:08.802
Okay, just stop squirming.
Would you just... Hey!

487
00:39:09.483 --> 00:39:12.932
Okay, okay, okay.
I'm letting go. I am letting go.

488
00:39:17.516 --> 00:39:19.207
This is not working.

489
00:39:21.806 --> 00:39:25.123
Hey, maybe that guy can help.
He's a really good flyer.

490
00:39:26.574 --> 00:39:27.981
Hey, up there!

491
00:39:31.374 --> 00:39:32.422
Hawk!

492
00:39:42.864 --> 00:39:44.172
- What's happening?
- Quick, hide!

493
00:39:44.272 --> 00:39:45.482
Look out!

494
00:39:50.992 --> 00:39:53.294
A hawk! Tinker Bell's in trouble!

495
00:40:06.931 --> 00:40:08.142
- Hey!
- Vidia?

496
00:40:08.243 --> 00:40:10.065
This is my hiding spot!

497
00:40:12.084 --> 00:40:13.906
But it's all yours, now.

498
00:40:16.532 --> 00:40:17.515
No!

499
00:40:27.989 --> 00:40:31.022
- Get him!
- Get him!

500
00:40:36.245 --> 00:40:38.701
- What?
- You all right?

501
00:40:40.278 --> 00:40:41.391
So scary.

502
00:40:48.663 --> 00:40:50.354
Are you okay, Vidia?

503
00:40:53.625 --> 00:40:55.664
- Let me help you.
- Don't touch me! I'm fine!

504
00:40:55.768 --> 00:40:58.899
- But I was only trying to help.
- Well, stop trying.

505
00:41:03.545 --> 00:41:04.974
Tinker Bell...

506
00:41:06.425 --> 00:41:08.914
I can't hold water. I can't hold light.

507
00:41:09.018 --> 00:41:12.596
Birds hate me. I'm just so useless!

508
00:41:12.698 --> 00:41:13.843
Tink.

509
00:41:26.267 --> 00:41:29.050
Great.
I failed for the third time in a row.

510
00:41:30.011 --> 00:41:34.583
At this rate, I should get to
the mainland right about... Oh... Never!

511
00:41:36.701 --> 00:41:37.659
Huh?

512
00:42:29.219 --> 00:42:30.233
Yes!

513
00:42:38.916 --> 00:42:39.930
Sil!

514
00:43:23.241 --> 00:43:24.484
Beautiful.

515
00:43:52.044 --> 00:43:53.451
- You fixed it!
- Wow!

516
00:43:53.612 --> 00:43:55.369
- Beautiful!
- Amazing!

517
00:43:55.469 --> 00:43:56.502
What are you guys doing here?

518
00:43:56.525 --> 00:43:59.275
It might be
the sparkliest thing I've ever seen,

519
00:43:59.374 --> 00:44:00.836
and I've seen a lot of sparkly things!

520
00:44:00.942 --> 00:44:05.099
It's a really pretty thingy. What is it?

521
00:44:05.422 --> 00:44:07.048
I don't know. I just found it.

522
00:44:07.150 --> 00:44:11.372
Tinker Bell, don't you even realize
what you're doing? You're tinkering!

523
00:44:11.663 --> 00:44:14.958
What? No, no, this isn't... I was just...

524
00:44:15.247 --> 00:44:19.241
Creating those gadgets,
figuring things out, fixing stuff like this,

525
00:44:19.535 --> 00:44:21.226
that's what tinkering is, sweetie!

526
00:44:21.326 --> 00:44:24.644
Don't you like doing this?
Isn't it what you really love?

527
00:44:24.751 --> 00:44:27.173
Yeah! Who cares about
going to the mainland, anyway?

528
00:44:27.280 --> 00:44:29.516
Well, I do, remember?

529
00:44:30.160 --> 00:44:32.298
I want to see
where these things come from.

530
00:44:32.400 --> 00:44:34.637
Why are you saying this?
Are you just giving up on me?

531
00:44:34.737 --> 00:44:38.087
I mean, aren't you going to teach me
to be a garden fairy anymore?

532
00:44:38.193 --> 00:44:40.779
Sweet pea, I think this is your talent.

533
00:44:41.362 --> 00:44:43.500
Tink, we just want you to be happy.

534
00:44:43.602 --> 00:44:46.417
If you really want me to be happy,
you'll help me get to the mainland

535
00:44:46.515 --> 00:44:48.108
like you promised.

536
00:44:49.363 --> 00:44:52.429
Please, Tinker Bell, just think about it.

537
00:45:29.272 --> 00:45:32.239
Will you teach me how to be
a fast-flying fairy?

538
00:45:34.551 --> 00:45:36.657
Please? I know I could do it!

539
00:45:36.792 --> 00:45:40.371
With your help, I could be flying
as fast as you in no time.

540
00:45:40.601 --> 00:45:44.595
Vidia, you're my last hope.
All my friends have given up on me.

541
00:45:46.042 --> 00:45:49.620
Rosetta won't even try to teach me
to be a garden fairy now.

542
00:45:50.042 --> 00:45:54.615
I bet I could at least paint some flowers
or plant some sproutlings.

543
00:45:55.130 --> 00:45:57.848
I mean,
there must be something I could do.

544
00:46:00.507 --> 00:46:03.856
Or if you really want to be
a garden fairy...

545
00:46:14.268 --> 00:46:16.473
Capture the sprinting thistles.

546
00:46:17.533 --> 00:46:21.494
Well, okay. I can do this. Yeah!

547
00:46:23.582 --> 00:46:25.273
Okay. Ready, Cheese?

548
00:46:27.934 --> 00:46:29.974
Come on. They're just weeds.

549
00:46:32.318 --> 00:46:35.865
Besides, there were only
seven or eight at the most, right?

550
00:46:40.480 --> 00:46:41.528
Hyah!

551
00:46:46.112 --> 00:46:50.368
We can do this. I know we can do this.
What do you say?

552
00:46:54.145 --> 00:46:55.323
Attaboy.

553
00:47:05.378 --> 00:47:07.167
This ought to be good.

554
00:47:19.044 --> 00:47:20.090
Hey!

555
00:47:20.197 --> 00:47:22.651
Come on, you!
Oh, come on!

556
00:47:23.269 --> 00:47:27.644
Just a bit this way!
It's working! It's working!

557
00:47:35.399 --> 00:47:36.576
Come on!

558
00:47:43.784 --> 00:47:46.599
Wait, wait, wait.
Come back! Come back!

559
00:47:48.806 --> 00:47:54.436
These things just won't listen!
Come on, Cheese. Go, go, go!

560
00:48:00.040 --> 00:48:02.342
Okay, definitely more than eight.

561
00:48:04.136 --> 00:48:07.170
Please file into the corral
in an orderly manner!

562
00:48:10.024 --> 00:48:11.072
Wait!

563
00:48:13.706 --> 00:48:15.495
Oh, no! Come on!

564
00:48:21.388 --> 00:48:22.795
Come on, now.

565
00:48:32.012 --> 00:48:34.695
Sorry. Sorry.
Excuse me. So sorry.

566
00:48:34.860 --> 00:48:36.683
This is the last batch.

567
00:48:40.686 --> 00:48:41.896
Look out!

568
00:48:42.286 --> 00:48:43.845
Sorry. Sorry!

569
00:49:35.443 --> 00:49:36.589
Oh, no.

570
00:49:36.756 --> 00:49:38.315
Tink. What happened?

571
00:49:38.419 --> 00:49:39.761
- I...
- Tinker Bell,

572
00:49:39.859 --> 00:49:41.201
what did you think you were doing?

573
00:49:41.299 --> 00:49:43.721
I was just... I was just trying to...

574
00:49:43.827 --> 00:49:45.770
I thought if I could capture
the thistles, then...

575
00:49:45.877 --> 00:49:49.390
There isn't a garden fairy alive
who can control those weeds!

576
00:49:49.492 --> 00:49:52.078
- What were you trying to prove?
- I...

577
00:49:52.181 --> 00:49:54.996
She's right, Tink.
This has all gone too far.

578
00:49:58.773 --> 00:50:00.683
By the second star!

579
00:50:03.350 --> 00:50:06.417
All the preparations for spring...
How did this...

580
00:50:14.487 --> 00:50:19.278
Queen Clarion, it was me.

581
00:50:20.056 --> 00:50:22.326
I did it. It was all my fault.

582
00:50:23.289 --> 00:50:24.631
Tinker Bell.

583
00:50:25.785 --> 00:50:27.192
I...

584
00:50:28.153 --> 00:50:29.430
I'm sorry.

585
00:50:44.379 --> 00:50:46.714
I don't think we can
fix this in time.

586
00:50:46.812 --> 00:50:49.747
We're going to have to cancel spring,
or postpone it at the very least.

587
00:50:49.852 --> 00:50:52.023
What, and put my
snowflake fairies back to work? Oh, no.

588
00:50:52.124 --> 00:50:53.652
But we can't! We can't do that!

589
00:50:53.756 --> 00:50:54.868
If the snow isn't melted,

590
00:50:54.972 --> 00:50:57.061
the seedlings won't grow,
the fruit won't ripen in the summer...

591
00:50:57.084 --> 00:50:59.386
And in the autumn,
there will be nothing to harvest.

592
00:50:59.485 --> 00:51:00.794
Spring must happen on time,

593
00:51:00.893 --> 00:51:02.551
or the balance of nature
will be undone!

594
00:51:02.653 --> 00:51:05.620
There must be something we can do!
Certainly this has happened before!

595
00:51:05.725 --> 00:51:07.864
It has!
Did you ever hear of the Ice Age?

596
00:51:07.966 --> 00:51:09.853
Settle down, all of you.

597
00:51:10.623 --> 00:51:14.879
Fairy Mary, is it even possible to redo
everything in such a short time?

598
00:51:20.735 --> 00:51:23.037
- No.
- Oh, no.

599
00:51:23.136 --> 00:51:25.558
We were so close,
and now it's all gone.

600
00:51:25.665 --> 00:51:27.289
Who's going to paint
our leaves now?

601
00:51:27.392 --> 00:51:28.985
The apples and pumpkins
will never grow.

602
00:51:29.087 --> 00:51:30.998
No rolling hills
covered in daffodils?

603
00:51:31.104 --> 00:51:33.079
And it took months to harvest
all those seeds!

604
00:51:33.184 --> 00:51:34.559
Animals waking
from hibernation

605
00:51:34.656 --> 00:51:36.545
will have nothing to eat!

606
00:52:03.140 --> 00:52:04.602
You okay, Tink?

607
00:52:05.701 --> 00:52:07.708
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

608
00:52:08.645 --> 00:52:13.402
I just came hoping to get a quick refill.
I'm going away for a while.

609
00:52:14.182 --> 00:52:15.141
Oh.

610
00:52:15.559 --> 00:52:19.487
- Well, how long you going to be gone?
- Well, actually, forever.

611
00:52:21.255 --> 00:52:22.912
Forever? Well,

612
00:52:24.486 --> 00:52:27.040
in that case,
a double scoop.

613
00:52:27.590 --> 00:52:30.143
Forever's a pretty long time, so I hear.

614
00:52:30.247 --> 00:52:31.676
Thanks, Terence.

615
00:52:31.782 --> 00:52:33.343
You know my name?

616
00:52:33.447 --> 00:52:35.716
Well, sure. Why wouldn't I?

617
00:52:36.039 --> 00:52:38.658
I don't know.
I'm just a dust-keeper guy.

618
00:52:39.592 --> 00:52:42.560
I'm not exactly seen as the most
important fairy in Pixie Hollow.

619
00:52:42.664 --> 00:52:44.487
Terence, what are you talking about?

620
00:52:44.585 --> 00:52:46.919
You're probably the most important one
there is!

621
00:52:47.017 --> 00:52:49.221
Without you,
no one would have any magic!

622
00:52:49.321 --> 00:52:51.907
Why, your talent makes you
who you are!

623
00:52:52.426 --> 00:52:55.208
- You should be proud of it! I mean...
- I am.

624
00:53:03.627 --> 00:53:06.377
I'd better get going.

625
00:53:42.127 --> 00:53:43.469
Hey, Cheese.

626
00:53:45.712 --> 00:53:48.330
"Be proud of your talent." What talent?

627
00:53:48.816 --> 00:53:51.751
I couldn't even get
these silly things to work.

628
00:54:04.434 --> 00:54:05.776
Lost things.

629
00:54:20.595 --> 00:54:21.872
That's it!

630
00:54:30.996 --> 00:54:32.688
Attention, everyone!

631
00:54:34.325 --> 00:54:36.715
I'm afraid I have distressing news.

632
00:54:38.262 --> 00:54:40.945
There is no way spring
can come on time.

633
00:54:41.782 --> 00:54:43.987
Months of work was lost,

634
00:54:44.086 --> 00:54:46.542
and it will take us months
to restore it all.

635
00:54:47.255 --> 00:54:49.776
So when the Everblossom
opens tomorrow,

636
00:54:50.136 --> 00:54:53.682
I'm afraid we will not be going
to the mainland for spring.

637
00:54:55.703 --> 00:54:58.551
Wait! I know how we can fix everything!

638
00:54:59.960 --> 00:55:01.302
Tinker Bell?

639
00:55:03.865 --> 00:55:05.720
Tinker Bell, I don't think this is...

640
00:55:05.818 --> 00:55:08.632
Just hear me out. Please.

641
00:55:09.721 --> 00:55:10.736
You!

642
00:55:13.913 --> 00:55:16.499
How long does it take you
to paint a ladybug?

643
00:55:16.602 --> 00:55:19.384
I don't know. 10, 15 minutes, I guess.

644
00:55:36.413 --> 00:55:40.025
See? We can build more.
I can show you how.

645
00:55:40.124 --> 00:55:43.671
Making paint, gathering seeds,
we can do it all in no time.

646
00:55:44.221 --> 00:55:46.109
We have to at least try!

647
00:55:46.910 --> 00:55:49.845
Wait a...
Are we really gonna listen to her?

648
00:55:50.110 --> 00:55:52.566
She's the reason we're in this mess
in the first place!

649
00:55:52.670 --> 00:55:54.427
But I can fix it.

650
00:55:54.527 --> 00:55:58.935
Yippee! Tinker Bell's going to save us
with her dopey little doohickeys.

651
00:55:59.423 --> 00:56:02.488
- Hide the squirrels!
- What is your problem, Vidia?

652
00:56:02.622 --> 00:56:04.360
Why do you think
you're so much better than me?

653
00:56:04.383 --> 00:56:07.700
I am better than you, sweetie.
I didn't ruin spring.

654
00:56:07.807 --> 00:56:09.815
At least now I'm trying to help.

655
00:56:09.920 --> 00:56:12.254
Have you ever helped anyone
besides yourself?

656
00:56:12.352 --> 00:56:14.076
Well, I tried to help you!

657
00:56:14.176 --> 00:56:15.998
Maybe I should have told you
to capture the hawk

658
00:56:16.096 --> 00:56:17.952
instead of the thistles!

659
00:56:25.339 --> 00:56:28.339
Perhaps Tinker Bell was not
the only one responsible.

660
00:56:30.299 --> 00:56:33.846
It seems to me that
your fast-flying talent is well-suited

661
00:56:33.948 --> 00:56:37.210
to chasing down each and every one
of the thistles.

662
00:56:37.533 --> 00:56:38.514
Me?

663
00:56:38.749 --> 00:56:42.164
Yes. And I expect them all
to be returned to Needlepoint Meadow

664
00:56:42.269 --> 00:56:43.228
as soon as possible.

665
00:56:43.325 --> 00:56:45.628
But that could take forever!

666
00:56:45.726 --> 00:56:47.930
Then I suggest you get started.

667
00:56:57.247 --> 00:57:01.502
Now, Tinker Bell,
are you sure you can do this?

668
00:57:04.384 --> 00:57:05.399
Yes.

669
00:57:06.688 --> 00:57:10.168
Because I'm a tinker. It's who I am.

670
00:57:12.097 --> 00:57:13.919
And tinkers fix things.

671
00:57:15.457 --> 00:57:17.344
But I can't do it alone.

672
00:57:20.673 --> 00:57:22.462
Command us, Miss Bell.

673
00:57:23.170 --> 00:57:25.080
- I'll help.
- Show us how, Tink!

674
00:57:25.186 --> 00:57:27.073
- I'll help you.
- Me, too!

675
00:57:27.331 --> 00:57:32.798
Okay, gather up all the twigs you can,
all different sizes, and tree sap.

676
00:57:32.899 --> 00:57:36.128
We need lots of that.
But most importantly,

677
00:57:36.228 --> 00:57:39.610
we need to find lost things.

678
00:57:48.038 --> 00:57:49.663
Okay, what have you got?

679
00:57:49.766 --> 00:57:51.674
- How about this?
- Will this do?

680
00:57:51.781 --> 00:57:53.789
Can you use this fuzzy thing,
Miss Bell?

681
00:57:53.893 --> 00:57:55.202
- Oh, yeah!
- It's not fuzzy.

682
00:57:55.301 --> 00:57:57.635
- Yes, it is.
- No, it isn't.

683
00:58:00.806 --> 00:58:01.984
Twig.

684
00:58:02.086 --> 00:58:03.613
Hammer.

685
00:58:03.719 --> 00:58:06.469
Magnification, please. Thank you.

686
00:58:08.582 --> 00:58:10.470
And that's how you do it!

687
00:58:12.583 --> 00:58:14.755
Now, what do you suppose the...

688
00:58:25.546 --> 00:58:27.073
You smell funny.

689
00:58:28.682 --> 00:58:29.642
Oh!

690
00:58:31.594 --> 00:58:33.896
- I saw it first.
- I bumped into it.

691
00:58:34.698 --> 00:58:36.608
Just tie this off here.

692
00:58:37.034 --> 00:58:41.541
So, you just squeeze this,
then let it go, and...

693
00:58:42.795 --> 00:58:44.486
See? Simple!

694
00:58:47.371 --> 00:58:48.549
Now, just put the berries in,

695
00:58:48.651 --> 00:58:50.626
and we'll have plenty of paint
in no time!

696
00:59:25.360 --> 00:59:28.622
Six, seven and eight.

697
01:00:22.742 --> 01:00:26.092
You did it, Tinker Bell.
You saved spring.

698
01:00:27.480 --> 01:00:28.757
We all did it.

699
01:00:28.855 --> 01:00:31.889
Queen Clarion? Can't Tink
come with us to the mainland?

700
01:00:31.992 --> 01:00:34.893
Yeah, she's done so much
for everyone.

701
01:00:35.159 --> 01:00:38.421
No, no, you guys, really.
I don't need to go.

702
01:00:39.159 --> 01:00:41.069
Buttercup, it's what you wanted.

703
01:00:41.176 --> 01:00:43.632
It's okay. My work is here.

704
01:00:43.736 --> 01:00:45.624
And I still have so much to do. I gotta...

705
01:00:45.721 --> 01:00:47.412
Not here, you don't!

706
01:00:47.577 --> 01:00:49.268
Well... But I don't...

707
01:00:51.226 --> 01:00:52.470
Surprise, Miss Bell.

708
01:00:52.570 --> 01:00:55.417
We found your tiny dancer!

709
01:00:56.922 --> 01:01:00.086
Actually, I ran across this myself
many seasons ago.

710
01:01:00.667 --> 01:01:03.799
I didn't have a clue what it was
or how to fix it.

711
01:01:04.474 --> 01:01:09.461
But you did, Tinker Bell.
You are quite a rare talent indeed.

712
01:01:10.492 --> 01:01:14.452
And I'd imagine there's a little girl
out there who's missing this.

713
01:01:15.165 --> 01:01:17.052
What do you mean? How...

714
01:01:17.149 --> 01:01:19.702
I think that perhaps
a certain tinker fairy

715
01:01:19.805 --> 01:01:22.227
might have a job to do after all,

716
01:01:22.333 --> 01:01:23.577
on the mainland.

717
01:01:23.677 --> 01:01:25.139
You mean, I...

718
01:01:28.734 --> 01:01:30.055
- I knew you'd get to go!
- Oh, Tink!

719
01:01:30.078 --> 01:01:32.052
- We can help, Miss Bell.
- We can help. I'm strong.

720
01:01:32.158 --> 01:01:35.258
I'm so happy for you.
Come on. We gotta go line up.

721
01:01:36.286 --> 01:01:38.174
Thank you, Your Highness.

722
01:01:38.271 --> 01:01:40.638
But how will I find who it belongs to?

723
01:01:40.735 --> 01:01:42.558
You'll know. Now go!

724
01:01:50.367 --> 01:01:51.775
Good heavens.

725
01:01:52.544 --> 01:01:53.788
Thank you.

726
01:01:59.138 --> 01:02:02.171
Tink. Hey,
something to help you on the mainland.

727
01:02:04.321 --> 01:02:06.232
Terence, that's so sweet.

728
01:02:08.739 --> 01:02:10.266
Good luck, Tink.

729
01:02:10.659 --> 01:02:14.457
To the air, fairies! To the air!
The mainland awaits!

730
01:02:16.068 --> 01:02:20.770
<i>Come away
with me now to the sky</i>

731
01:02:20.868 --> 01:02:24.610
<i>Up o'er the hills and the sea</i>

732
01:02:24.708 --> 01:02:28.931
<i>Far beyond where our memories lie</i>

733
01:02:29.028 --> 01:02:33.152
<i>To a place where I'm free to be me</i>

734
01:02:35.430 --> 01:02:39.107
<i>Oh gather ye now one and all</i>

735
01:02:39.206 --> 01:02:43.713
<i>No matter what all ye may do</i>

736
01:02:43.815 --> 01:02:48.387
<i>Let the stars fill your soul
when the moon cradles all</i>

737
01:02:48.486 --> 01:02:53.190
<i>So to yourself be true</i>

738
01:02:54.535 --> 01:02:59.108
<i>The blanket of snow is all gone</i>

